The paper deals with the segmentation of retinal morphology using deep learning methods, specifically focusing on the task of retinal vessel segmentation. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of batch normalization and computational efficiency, which are topics commonly associated with machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of multimedia image registration, which could potentially fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
